          <h2 style="font-size:24px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500; margin-top:2px !important">Hezbollah leader funeral</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/hassan-nasrallah-hashem-safieddine-funeral-beirut-lebanon.png" alt="People gather for the funeral ceremony of Lebanon's late Hezbollah leaders Hassan Nasrallah and Hashem Safieddine at the Sports City Stadium in Beirut, Lebanon" href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;">People gather for the funeral ceremony of Lebanon's late Hezbollah leaders Hassan Nasrallah and Hashem Safieddine at the Sports City Stadium in Beirut, Lebanon. Credits: Hassan Ammar/AP</p>
        </mj-text> 

        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
         
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Hezbollah leader Hassan Nasrallah's funeral was held in Beirut on Sunday. This came nearly <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-25-02-2025-h1-1-five-months-after-he-died?source=website" target="_blank">five months after he died</a> in an Israeli airstrike. The public funeral was held on Sunday at Beirut’s Camille Chamoun Sports City Stadium. Lebanese media said Israel disrupted the event with air attacks and low-flying jets. Since 1992, Nasrallah has built Hezbollah into a strong regional force.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Hezbollah official Ali Daamoush told reporters that about 800 personalities from 65 countries would attend the funeral. Experts say the funeral was a show of force and displayed their power to mobilize people from different parts of Lebanon. Nasrallah will be buried in a piece of land near the airport road in Beirut’s southern suburbs.  
       </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Hezbollah faced heavy losses after backing Hamas in the 2023 Israel-Gaza war. Israel's strikes and assassinations have weakened Hezbollah, and Lebanon's president has called for its disarmament. Israel continues to target the group, creating uncertainty about its future. Though the Israeli army withdrew from southern Lebanese towns on Tuesday, it maintains a military presence at five border outposts.
</p>
        </mj-text>
