            <strong>🇯🇵 Japan and Philippines boost military ties amid Asia Pacific region tensions</strong>
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Japan and the Philippines are joining forces to <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-25-02-2025-br1-4-deepen-their-defense-against-china?source=website" target="_blank">deepen their defense against China's aggressive actions</a>. Japanese DM Gen Nakatani and his Philippine counterpart Gilberto Teodoro met in Manila. They focused on joint defense training, port visits, and sharing military information. They also discussed a plan to protect their shared military intelligence.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Due to China's recent actions in the South and East China Seas, both countries are boosting their military ties. Last year, they signed an agreement for joint military exercises in each other's territories. Japan is also increasing its military capabilities and plans to double its defense spending by 2027. Also high on the agenda was the expansion of bilateral cooperation, especially in the context of the Reciprocal Access Agreement.</p>
        </mj-text>
