          <p style="font-size:18px;line-height:1.5;">
            <strong>🇩🇪 Germany’s Friedrich Merz calls for ‘independence’ from US after election win.</strong>
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Friedrich Merz, Germany’s next chancellor, is pushing Europe <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-25-02-2025-br2-5-to-rely-less-on-us-for-its-security?source=website" target="_blank">to rely less on the US for its security</a>, citing indifference under Trump. Merz, who was once a strong Atlanticist, challenges NATO’s future and urges Europe to boost its defense. Germany, already Ukraine’s second-largest military donor, may seek a nuclear umbrella with France and the UK.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Merz faces several domestic challenges, including a weak economy, tense coalition talks, and public fears about migration. His changing views reflect those of many European leaders. However, implementing these plans needs substantial funding and cooperation from European allies, who may be reluctant to sever ties with the US.</p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
